---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Retiree Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pre-existing', text: 'Pre-existing Conditions', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Retiree Insurance', href: '/best/retiree-insurance' },
  { title: 'Senior Insurance', href: '/best/senior-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Max Entry Age', bupa: 'No limit', cigna: 'No limit', allianz: '74 years' },
  { feature: 'Lifetime Renewal', bupa: 'Guaranteed', cigna: 'Guaranteed', allianz: 'Guaranteed' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Handling', bupa: 'Moratorium/Full UW', cigna: 'Moratorium/Full UW', allianz: 'More flexible' },
  { feature: 'Chronic Condition Mgmt', bupa: 'Excellent', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Very Good' },
  { feature: 'No-Claims Discount', bupa: 'Yes (up to 50%)', cigna: 'No', allianz: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Wellness Programs', bupa: 'Good', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Claims Speed', bupa: '5-7 days', cigna: '5-10 days', allianz: '10-15 days' },
  { feature: 'Price (60+)', bupa: 'Premium', cigna: 'Premium', allianz: 'Value' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 55', bupa: '$400-520/mo', cigna: '$380-480/mo', allianz: '$320-400/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 60', bupa: '$520-680/mo', cigna: '$480-620/mo', allianz: '$400-520/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 65', bupa: '$680-880/mo', cigna: '$620-800/mo', allianz: '$520-680/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 60', bupa: '$980-1280/mo', cigna: '$900-1160/mo', allianz: '$760-980/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 70', bupa: '$900-1200/mo', cigna: '$820-1080/mo', allianz: '$680-880/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Bupa vs Cigna vs Allianz: Best Insurance for Expat Retirees 2026"
  description="Compare the top insurers for expat retirees: Bupa Global, Cigna Global, and Allianz Care. Lifetime renewal, pre-existing conditions, and retiree pricing compared."
  headline="Bupa vs Cigna vs Allianz: Best for Expat Retirees"
  subheadline="Retiring abroad? These three insurers offer lifetime coverage with no age limits. Here's how they compare for retirees."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for Healthy Retirees</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">No-claims discount rewards healthy retirees. Premium service. Fastest claims when you need them.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Network</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Largest network for specialist access. Best app for managing care. Excellent chronic condition support.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">15-20% lower premiums. More flexible on pre-existing conditions. Entry age limit at 74.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    All three offer lifetime renewal guarantees—once you're in, they can't drop you for health reasons. The choice depends on your health status, budget, and where you plan to retire.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No-Claims Discount</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No Age Limit</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Fast Claims</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global is ideal for healthy retirees. Their unique no-claims discount can reduce your premiums by up to 50% if you rarely claim—a significant benefit when premiums increase with age. No maximum entry age means you can join even in your 80s.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Retiree Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>No-claims discount up to 50% (huge for retirees)</li>
    <li>No maximum entry age</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guaranteed</li>
    <li>Fastest claims processing (5-7 days)</li>
    <li>Premium service for complex health needs</li>
    <li>Strong chronic condition management</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Highest starting premiums</li>
    <li>No-claims discount lost if you claim</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions may be excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Healthy retirees who rarely need healthcare. Those planning 10+ years of coverage (no-claims discount compounds). Retirees who value premium service.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Largest Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Specialist Access</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global's massive network is particularly valuable for retirees who may need specialist care. With 1.5M+ providers worldwide, you'll have access to cardiologists, oncologists, and other specialists wherever you retire. Their app makes managing multiple prescriptions and appointments easy.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Retiree Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Largest global network (1.5M+ providers)</li>
    <li>Excellent specialist access</li>
    <li>Best mobile app for health management</li>
    <li>Strong chronic condition programs</li>
    <li>Wellness programs and preventive care</li>
    <li>No maximum entry age</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guaranteed</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>No no-claims discount</li>
    <li>Premium pricing</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions may face exclusions</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Retirees who expect to use healthcare regularly. Those with chronic conditions needing specialist access. Tech-comfortable retirees who'll use the app.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Pre-existing</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Europe Expert</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care offers the most affordable option for retirees, with premiums 15-20% below Cigna and Bupa. They're also generally more flexible with pre-existing conditions, often offering coverage with premium loadings rather than outright exclusions.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Retiree Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>15-20% lower premiums than competitors</li>
    <li>More flexible pre-existing condition terms</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guaranteed</li>
    <li>Strong European network (popular retiree destinations)</li>
    <li>Good chronic condition management</li>
    <li>German reliability</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Maximum entry age of 74</li>
    <li>Slower claims processing (10-15 days)</li>
    <li>Smaller network than Cigna</li>
    <li>No no-claims discount</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious retirees under 74. Those with pre-existing conditions needing coverage. Retirees in Europe. Those who don't need premium service.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Retiree Plans"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Bupa, Cigna, and Allianz based on your age and health status."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Retiree Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Insurance premiums increase significantly with age. Here's what retirees can expect to pay for comprehensive coverage excluding US:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive plans excluding US coverage. Actual quotes vary based on health status and coverage selections.
  </p>

  <h3>Understanding Retiree Premiums</h3>

  <p>
    Premiums increase with age because healthcare costs rise. A 70-year-old typically costs insurers 3-4x more than a 40-year-old. Budget for annual increases of 5-10% beyond normal inflation as you age.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa's no-claims discount matters here:</strong> If you're healthy and rarely claim, Bupa's 50% discount can make them cheaper than Allianz within a few years—and that discount compounds over decades of retirement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pre-existing">Pre-existing Conditions</h2>

  <p>
    Most retirees have some health history. Here's how each insurer handles pre-existing conditions:
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Moratorium underwriting: conditions excluded for 2 years, then may be covered if treatment-free</li>
    <li>Full medical underwriting available: they review history and decide</li>
    <li>May exclude specific conditions permanently</li>
    <li>Well-managed conditions often accepted with waiting periods</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Similar moratorium and full underwriting options</li>
    <li>Slightly more accommodating for stable conditions</li>
    <li>Chronic conditions like controlled diabetes often covered</li>
    <li>Case-by-case evaluation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Generally most flexible of the three</li>
    <li>More likely to offer coverage with premium loading vs exclusion</li>
    <li>Good for stable, well-managed conditions</li>
    <li>European regulatory background influences approach</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <strong>Key advice:</strong> Apply to all three and compare the specific terms offered. Pre-existing condition handling varies significantly by individual case.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are generally healthy and rarely need healthcare</li>
        <li>Want to earn no-claims discounts over time</li>
        <li>Value premium service and fast claims</li>
        <li>Plan to keep coverage for 10+ years</li>
        <li>Can afford higher starting premiums</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have chronic conditions requiring regular specialist care</li>
        <li>Want the largest provider network worldwide</li>
        <li>Value a great mobile app for health management</li>
        <li>Plan to travel frequently in retirement</li>
        <li>Expect to use healthcare services regularly</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are under 74 and want affordable coverage</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions needing coverage</li>
        <li>Plan to retire in Europe</li>
        <li>Need to keep insurance costs manageable</li>
        <li>Don't require premium service or fast claims</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is there an age limit for international health insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa and Cigna have no maximum entry age—you can join at any age. Allianz Care has a maximum entry age of 74. Once enrolled, all three guarantee lifetime renewal regardless of age or health changes.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens to my premiums as I age?</h3>
  <p>
    Premiums increase with age on all policies, typically 5-10% annually beyond normal inflation. This reflects higher healthcare costs as you age. Budget for this when planning retirement finances.
  </p>

  <h3>Will pre-existing conditions be covered?</h3>
  <p>
    It depends on the condition and insurer. All three evaluate pre-existing conditions case-by-case. Allianz is generally most flexible. Apply to multiple insurers and compare the specific terms offered for your conditions.
  </p>

  <h3>Can they cancel my policy if I get sick?</h3>
  <p>
    No. All three offer lifetime renewal guarantees. Once you're enrolled, they cannot cancel your policy or refuse renewal due to health changes or claims. This is crucial protection for retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I'm over 74 and want coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Choose Bupa or Cigna, which have no maximum entry age. Allianz won't accept new members over 74, but if you're already enrolled with them before 74, you can keep your coverage for life.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I get coverage before or after retiring abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Before. It's easier to get coverage while younger and healthier. Any conditions that develop after enrollment are covered under your policy, while conditions you have when applying may be excluded.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
